WEBVTT

00:57.098 --> 00:58.183
I...

00:59.267 --> 01:00.852
don't want to get married.

01:09.861 --> 01:10.862
Are you saying

01:13.073 --> 01:15.992
that you won't marry my son?

01:17.494 --> 01:20.371
It's why I asked
to talk to you alone today.

01:21.831 --> 01:23.416
It's not Gi-seok's fault.

01:25.168 --> 01:26.753
If he were here,

01:27.420 --> 01:30.924
he would've made it out to be though.

01:32.425 --> 01:34.135
However, that's not the case.

01:36.513 --> 01:37.555
We...

01:38.765 --> 01:40.975
just failed one another.

01:45.480 --> 01:48.733
EPISODE 8

01:59.994 --> 02:02.330
I guess we should've talked sooner.

02:05.250 --> 02:06.376
Take care, then.

02:31.025 --> 02:32.735
Kid, what's wrong?

02:32.819 --> 02:34.696
Why? Gosh, it's all right.

02:34.779 --> 02:36.114
Where's your mom?

02:36.573 --> 02:38.283
Do you know where your mom is?

02:40.869 --> 02:42.954
Your mom will be soon. It's all right.

02:43.037 --> 02:44.414
- Eun-u.
- There she is.

02:44.497 --> 02:45.874
Gosh, she's here.

02:45.957 --> 02:48.084
What's wrong?

02:48.793 --> 02:49.919
Daddy...

02:50.461 --> 02:52.130
I can't find my dad.

02:52.255 --> 02:54.174
It's all right.

02:55.425 --> 02:57.677
Don't cry, Eun-u.
Your dad will be here soon.

03:00.471 --> 03:02.223
It's okay. I'm here, aren't I?

03:02.640 --> 03:03.725
Ms. Lee!

03:05.101 --> 03:06.144
What a relief.

03:08.021 --> 03:09.272
I think she is his teacher.

03:10.398 --> 03:11.858
- It's all right.
- Take care.

03:12.150 --> 03:13.318
Thank you.

03:13.735 --> 03:14.944
You're good now.

03:15.028 --> 03:16.362
SEONGDONG PUBLIC LIBRARY

03:21.618 --> 03:22.869
It's all right.

03:28.124 --> 03:30.168
- Eun-u, your dad's here.
- What's wrong?

03:31.169 --> 03:32.629
Dad!

03:33.046 --> 03:34.672
What's going on? Were you crying?

03:35.673 --> 03:36.758
It's all right.

03:38.551 --> 03:40.428
He was playing with the other kids, so...

03:43.014 --> 03:44.098
It's true.

03:45.600 --> 03:48.519
Eun-u, you're being a baby.
I was right outside.

03:48.603 --> 03:49.854
Are you blaming him again?

03:50.897 --> 03:51.940
Of course not.

03:54.651 --> 03:55.526
It's all right.

04:05.536 --> 04:08.456
CHILDREN'S READING ROOM

04:15.797 --> 04:18.925
Why did you bring him here
if you weren't going to watch him?

04:21.552 --> 04:23.304
See? He was fine on his own,

04:23.388 --> 04:25.348
so I just...

04:26.224 --> 04:29.852
stepped out to get some fresh air.

04:30.561 --> 04:32.897
It only takes seconds
for kids to get into trouble.

04:34.816 --> 04:36.317
You sound like you've raised one.

04:36.901 --> 04:39.654
I'm not a parent,
but even I know that it's wrong.

04:39.737 --> 04:41.864
But how could you, his father,
be so reckless?

04:44.158 --> 04:46.160
You're right.
I lack as a dad in many ways.

04:50.581 --> 04:52.750
- Are you sulking?
- As if.

04:54.335 --> 04:55.378
You are.

04:57.672 --> 04:58.881
Why are you here anyway?

05:00.967 --> 05:02.176
I work here, remember?

05:03.761 --> 05:04.929
But it's your day off.

05:06.973 --> 05:10.059
Did you choose to come today
because I wouldn't be here?

05:13.271 --> 05:14.105
Why?

05:16.274 --> 05:17.317
Isn't it obvious?

05:20.778 --> 05:23.865
I was quite happy to bump into you though.

05:24.991 --> 05:26.743
I guess that wasn't the case for you.

05:31.789 --> 05:33.416
Anyway, don't be too considerate.

05:35.168 --> 05:36.252
I'd prefer it that way.

05:45.386 --> 05:46.596
What are you doing here?

05:46.971 --> 05:48.431
- Why are you here?
- Your coffee.

05:49.265 --> 05:51.476
I needed to vent,
but you were at work today.

05:53.853 --> 05:56.397
Still, why come to the office
on your day off?

05:56.481 --> 05:57.523
You're insane.

06:01.402 --> 06:03.446
How did it go? Did you speak your mind?

06:04.822 --> 06:08.284
I guess. There's going to be
some serious blowback though.

06:09.994 --> 06:12.205
I see you set off the bomb.

06:15.708 --> 06:17.710
That pharmacist is here with his nephew.

06:19.253 --> 06:23.049
A young man spending time
with his nephew on his day off?

06:23.633 --> 06:26.260
That's not easy for anyone to do, right?

06:29.680 --> 06:30.640
What?

06:33.476 --> 06:34.310
Nothing.

06:37.939 --> 06:40.525
Are you breaking it off with Gi-seok next?

06:43.069 --> 06:45.154
How did Gi-seok and I end up here?

06:45.780 --> 06:48.116
That's how it is
with long-term relationships.

06:48.616 --> 06:51.411
The process of breaking up
begins before you even know it.

06:55.498 --> 06:56.457
It's not just that.

06:56.874 --> 06:59.669
I didn't even know I've been going through
the process myself,

06:59.919 --> 07:02.213
but I was brazen enough
to give others advice.

07:03.047 --> 07:03.965
To whom?

07:14.434 --> 07:16.227
If only you'd eat your meals this well.

07:18.938 --> 07:21.274
Did you get scared
when you couldn't find me?

07:22.400 --> 07:24.444
I thought you had abandoned me.

07:25.027 --> 07:27.363
That's absurd. Why would I ever do that?

07:27.947 --> 07:29.198
You were gone.

07:34.787 --> 07:39.584
But the teacher came,
so I wasn't scared anymore.

07:43.629 --> 07:44.755
Are you fond of her?

07:45.339 --> 07:47.133
- Yes.
- Why?

07:50.761 --> 07:51.846
She's nice.

07:53.431 --> 07:54.557
What about you?

07:56.434 --> 07:57.518
What do you mean?

07:58.102 --> 07:59.687
Are you fond of her too?

08:02.148 --> 08:03.024
Yes.

08:04.692 --> 08:06.277
- Why?
- What?

08:09.405 --> 08:10.490
Because she's nice.

08:17.330 --> 08:18.372
Dig in.

08:35.556 --> 08:37.600
- Are you going somewhere?
- To Jeong-in's.

08:38.142 --> 08:40.353
- What?
- She's not picking up.

08:40.603 --> 08:43.147
They must still be talking then.

08:43.981 --> 08:46.609
They'll part ways before dinner,
so I'll go there and wait.

08:46.692 --> 08:48.694
Tae-hak, please.

08:49.195 --> 08:51.489
I need to know what happened.

08:51.614 --> 08:53.199
I'm sure someone will call.

08:53.282 --> 08:55.868
Either Jeong-in or Mr. Kwon will call us.

08:56.327 --> 08:57.828
But she's not picking up.

08:59.205 --> 09:00.456
What's Mr. Kwon's number?

09:00.790 --> 09:01.999
Don't be like this.

09:02.416 --> 09:04.168
What's there to be scared of?

09:04.293 --> 09:06.462
As parents, we have the right to say

09:06.546 --> 09:08.506
that he should be nice to our daughter.

09:08.589 --> 09:09.715
Don't you dare.

09:11.050 --> 09:13.302
This is wrong, you know.

09:14.053 --> 09:16.847
I know he's your boss,
but family still comes first.

09:17.265 --> 09:19.684
Your family and children
should be your priority.

09:19.767 --> 09:21.811
You think I'm being a coward,

09:22.687 --> 09:25.273
but that's because
you don't know how he is.

09:25.648 --> 09:27.483
Once he makes up his mind,

09:27.567 --> 09:30.236
there's nothing you can do to change it.

09:52.216 --> 09:53.884
- Take me to Gi-seok's.
- Yes, sir.

10:04.395 --> 10:06.731
Can I get you some tea?

10:18.200 --> 10:19.535
Was the meeting with Jeong-in

10:20.536 --> 10:21.704
uncomfortable?

10:27.710 --> 10:29.086
She's a decent young woman.

10:31.005 --> 10:32.923
You don't see women like her these days.

10:34.050 --> 10:35.509
She's even more mature than you.

10:40.181 --> 10:41.474
It won't be easy.

10:42.975 --> 10:45.686
She's not the type
that you can easily contain.

10:49.190 --> 10:50.524
Try to think of it long-term.

10:51.984 --> 10:53.736
Like I said, she has a rare quality.

10:54.987 --> 10:56.864
Those rare are harder to obtain anyway.

11:23.140 --> 11:24.141
Do your best.

11:26.310 --> 11:28.020
- I will.
- Let's go.

12:21.407 --> 12:26.120
CHILDREN'S READING ROOM

13:11.499 --> 13:13.292
- Hi.
- Where are you?

13:15.294 --> 13:17.338
I had to stop by the office.

13:18.130 --> 13:20.382
It's just that you didn't call.

13:21.842 --> 13:23.302
How did it go with my father?

13:23.844 --> 13:25.054
Wasn't it uncomfortable?

13:25.596 --> 13:27.515
He was kind and generous.

13:29.767 --> 13:31.852
My father is quite the silent type,

13:32.686 --> 13:34.355
but I guess he liked you.

13:39.151 --> 13:40.444
I'm not busy, but...

13:41.654 --> 13:42.696
Wait, can you hold?

13:43.906 --> 13:46.408
- What are you looking for?
- The restock log.

13:46.617 --> 13:47.701
Oh, that.

13:48.285 --> 13:50.287
- Gi-seok, can I call you back--
- Sure.

13:54.625 --> 13:55.876
Isn't he pissed?

13:56.585 --> 13:58.462
Actually, he's being sweeter than usual.

13:59.380 --> 14:01.298
It's so like him though.

14:04.552 --> 14:06.428
He's not going down without a fight.

14:07.137 --> 14:10.349
He knows that you would've
spoken your mind to his father,

14:10.432 --> 14:12.059
so what else can it be?

14:12.518 --> 14:15.187
He's going to try and power through this.

14:24.822 --> 14:26.699
PHARMACIST

14:26.782 --> 14:27.908
We're heading out.

14:35.207 --> 14:36.375
Gosh, Jeong-in.

14:49.889 --> 14:51.348
I'm almost at the library.

14:51.432 --> 14:53.434
Take your time. I'll grab a cup of coffee.

14:58.939 --> 15:00.816
Let's have something nice for dinner.

15:01.025 --> 15:02.651
- Pork cutlet?
- Sure thing.

15:04.862 --> 15:06.071
What about Ms. Lee?

15:07.323 --> 15:09.325
She'll be down soon,
so be nice and proper.

15:09.825 --> 15:10.784
Okay.

15:12.828 --> 15:13.871
Ms. Lee!

15:22.838 --> 15:23.839
I'll be right back.

15:35.142 --> 15:36.226
What's wrong?

15:36.310 --> 15:37.978
Gi-seok's here.

15:40.522 --> 15:41.357
So?

15:42.483 --> 15:45.945
There's another exit
at the end of the hall.

15:50.157 --> 15:50.991
Ji-ho...

15:51.992 --> 15:54.036
Are you even going to
make my son miserable?

15:56.997 --> 15:58.540
I think you misunderstood me.

15:58.624 --> 16:00.292
No, this one's on you.

16:02.211 --> 16:04.380
You told me I don't have to be
too considerate.

16:05.923 --> 16:07.633
Why is this case any different?

16:12.054 --> 16:13.222
Eun-u isn't me.

16:14.556 --> 16:17.059
I can put up with anything, but not Eun-u.

16:18.978 --> 16:21.438
I won't forgive anyone who hurts my son.

16:36.120 --> 16:37.162
Let's go.

17:41.602 --> 17:42.603
Ji-ho?

17:46.106 --> 17:47.191
You should say hello.

17:47.858 --> 17:48.817
Hello.

17:49.943 --> 17:50.944
Oh, hi.

17:52.029 --> 17:52.946
Hi, there.

17:54.448 --> 17:56.158
You're quite handsome, aren't you?

17:59.578 --> 18:01.205
Didn't I see you here before too?

18:03.082 --> 18:04.625
You must come here often.

18:05.334 --> 18:07.669
Hyeon-su said you live near the pharmacy.

18:08.796 --> 18:10.172
I do.

18:11.465 --> 18:13.050
My girlfriend works here.

18:13.884 --> 18:14.718
Did you know that?

18:17.262 --> 18:18.388
Yes, I did.

18:20.974 --> 18:23.102
They have
a nice selection of children's books.

18:25.187 --> 18:26.396
I see.

18:26.939 --> 18:28.023
It's late, so...

18:29.066 --> 18:30.067
Oh, sure.

18:31.235 --> 18:32.319
Hold on.

18:36.406 --> 18:37.282
Wait.

18:39.993 --> 18:41.995
- Gi-seok, please.
- It's fine.

18:42.079 --> 18:43.163
- Please don't.
- Let go.

18:45.374 --> 18:47.668
Ask your dad to buy you
something delicious.

18:48.210 --> 18:49.211
Okay?

18:56.426 --> 18:57.427
Dad.

18:59.680 --> 19:02.516
Can we buy pork cutlet with this?

19:03.350 --> 19:05.227
- Yes.
- Yours too?

19:06.687 --> 19:07.688
Yes.

19:30.127 --> 19:32.629
SEONGDONG PUBLIC LIBRARY

19:47.144 --> 19:49.313
Hey, what's wrong?

19:52.482 --> 19:53.609
Why are you crying?

19:56.069 --> 19:57.112
Gi-seok.

19:58.530 --> 20:00.032
It's okay. Please don't cry.

20:01.825 --> 20:02.743
I'm sorry.

20:05.829 --> 20:06.705
What?

20:08.832 --> 20:09.875
I'm sorry, Gi-seok.

23:21.233 --> 23:24.277
CIVIL SERVICE EXAM CLASSES

23:24.361 --> 23:27.656
You shouldn't be late after
asking someone to buy you a meal.

23:28.365 --> 23:30.075
You're the one who offered.

23:30.367 --> 23:31.952
I'm still buying though.

23:32.536 --> 23:33.578
You're right.

23:33.995 --> 23:36.456
Your eyes are bloated.
Did you get into an argument?

23:37.582 --> 23:38.792
I ended it with Jae-in.

23:40.085 --> 23:41.211
You got dumped again?

23:43.004 --> 23:45.590
I'm the one who did the dumping.

23:47.217 --> 23:48.301
How so?

23:51.430 --> 23:52.764
You made the right choice.

23:54.558 --> 23:56.893
It's best to stay away from those sisters.

23:58.019 --> 24:02.023
Ji-ho might have fallen for her,
but it'll soon pass.

24:03.358 --> 24:06.486
He hasn't dated in quite a while.

24:06.987 --> 24:09.322
He could've mistaken kindness
for romantic feelings.

24:12.367 --> 24:13.702
You're desperate, aren't you?

24:15.036 --> 24:17.330
This just can't happen.

24:18.039 --> 24:20.333
We need to stop him.
He's no match for Gi-seok.

24:20.417 --> 24:21.293
Who can stop him?

24:21.376 --> 24:24.254
Have you seen him giving up
when he set his mind to something?

24:25.297 --> 24:26.506
You're right.

24:28.842 --> 24:29.926
Unbelievable.

24:30.302 --> 24:32.512
How can I face Gi-seok again
if this gets out?

24:33.597 --> 24:34.931
I guess it could get awkward.

24:35.390 --> 24:37.601
Still, it's wrong of him to blame others

24:37.934 --> 24:40.187
for his girlfriend falling out of love.

24:40.270 --> 24:41.521
Seriously?

24:42.147 --> 24:43.815
Someone's stealing his girlfriend.

24:44.649 --> 24:46.276
He can't think rationally.

24:47.152 --> 24:49.029
All he'll see is red.

24:50.864 --> 24:52.115
Let's call Ji-ho out.

24:52.282 --> 24:53.909
He went to the library with Eun-u.

24:55.869 --> 24:58.371
Shit. Are they having
family outings already?

24:58.955 --> 25:01.333
He mentioned going to the library before.

25:01.416 --> 25:04.336
I wonder if it was where Jeong-in works.

25:06.713 --> 25:08.882
He's lost his mind.

25:09.424 --> 25:10.926
Is he even thinking?

25:11.468 --> 25:12.761
What's making him so bold?

25:15.430 --> 25:18.058
- Jeong-in.
- Why is she being bold then?

25:19.351 --> 25:20.227
Ji-ho.

25:22.479 --> 25:23.772
What are you talking about?

25:25.815 --> 25:27.192
Love, you idiot.

25:33.865 --> 25:36.076
He was going to find out sooner or later.

25:37.953 --> 25:40.121
Although, he might feel
especially betrayed

25:40.205 --> 25:42.582
since it was on the day
you met his father.

25:44.584 --> 25:47.754
Ji-ho was furious when he left.

25:48.630 --> 25:50.215
Aren't you worried about Gi-seok?

25:51.424 --> 25:54.302
And the pharmacist isn't
in a position to get mad at you.

25:55.095 --> 25:56.179
He practically used

25:56.263 --> 25:58.181
his nephew to find an excuse to see you.

25:58.265 --> 25:59.933
That's not it.

26:00.141 --> 26:01.393
Of course it is.

26:01.476 --> 26:04.229
He felt awkward to come alone,
so he brought a child.

26:06.523 --> 26:09.442
- It's his son.
- Yes, I saw him. He's obviously a boy.

26:12.737 --> 26:13.613
Whose son?

26:15.282 --> 26:16.283
His son.

26:18.868 --> 26:19.995
He's Ji-ho's son.

26:23.623 --> 26:24.708
Hold on.

26:25.542 --> 26:26.543
Give me a second.

26:28.962 --> 26:30.714
Is the pharmacist married?

26:31.506 --> 26:32.549
Jeong-in!

26:34.634 --> 26:35.885
He's a single father.

26:37.053 --> 26:38.263
Gosh, Jeong-in.

26:39.264 --> 26:41.224
It's why I said I wasn't confident enough.

26:41.308 --> 26:43.226
This has nothing to do with confidence.

26:45.437 --> 26:46.980
What are you going to do?

26:53.862 --> 26:55.322
I'm lost right now.

26:57.699 --> 26:58.908
It's giving me a headache.

27:00.535 --> 27:01.578
Just wait a second.

27:17.385 --> 27:18.845
Did something bad happen?

27:21.890 --> 27:24.851
Mom, shall I meet the lady
you wanted to set me up with?

27:26.311 --> 27:27.312
Why?

27:28.146 --> 27:30.607
Just the other day,
you said there's someone you like.

27:32.484 --> 27:34.027
Because you wanted to set me up.

27:35.236 --> 27:37.322
You should date the one that you like.

27:39.282 --> 27:42.744
There's no guarantee that the one I like
will want to date someone like me.

27:43.953 --> 27:45.372
There's nothing wrong with you.

27:47.582 --> 27:49.876
Everyone has scars,
so you can just call it even.

27:50.502 --> 27:51.961
You don't lack anything.

27:52.337 --> 27:54.255
You're smart and good-looking.

27:54.506 --> 27:56.966
Plus, you have a good job.
You're a pretty good catch.

28:00.428 --> 28:02.639
So I shouldn't date someone
who isn't scarred?

28:03.390 --> 28:04.683
Obviously.

28:06.309 --> 28:09.437
Not everyone he meets
will be in the same situation as he is.

28:11.815 --> 28:13.024
Because of Eun-u?

28:14.359 --> 28:15.777
That is one of the reasons.

28:16.152 --> 28:19.531
But why would you want to put someone
without such a flaw through all that?

28:19.989 --> 28:22.492
That's selfish. It's bad karma.

28:22.575 --> 28:24.828
Don't even think that it may be possible.

28:30.959 --> 28:35.171
That lady you like...
Has she never been married?

28:37.674 --> 28:38.800
Give up immediately.

28:40.260 --> 28:41.177
No, just give up.

28:42.053 --> 28:44.681
Why are you jumping
to conclusions like that?

28:45.098 --> 28:48.518
Honey, you'd better not encourage him.

28:48.601 --> 28:50.103
It won't work out.

28:50.770 --> 28:51.855
Mom.

28:52.772 --> 28:54.357
No matter what it is, there is

28:54.441 --> 28:58.027
a world of difference between those who've
experienced it and those who haven't.

28:58.611 --> 29:00.196
She has no idea what it's like,

29:00.280 --> 29:02.115
and you'll expect her to understand you?

29:03.032 --> 29:05.618
That's so selfish. How unfair is that?

29:06.077 --> 29:07.328
Enough, stop.

29:11.916 --> 29:13.042
It's your life,

29:13.960 --> 29:15.170
so decide wisely.

29:16.212 --> 29:17.297
That's all you can do.

29:37.984 --> 29:40.403
Seo-in,
did you ask Si-hoon to meet you here?

29:40.653 --> 29:41.905
No, he's here for a show.

29:43.615 --> 29:44.783
What are you doing here?

29:55.543 --> 29:57.003
Jae-in, it's you.

29:58.129 --> 29:59.672
What are you doing here?

30:00.298 --> 30:02.050
And you should've called me.

30:02.133 --> 30:02.967
Why?

30:03.468 --> 30:05.887
What do you mean?
So that we can grab a meal together.

30:06.596 --> 30:07.847
She hasn't changed one bit.

30:08.181 --> 30:10.934
But your parents didn't mention
anything about Jae-in.

30:11.017 --> 30:13.728
They said nothing about her being back
when we visited them.

30:13.895 --> 30:15.230
She came back recently.

30:15.688 --> 30:18.274
- Shouldn't you head in--
- Hey, when shall we hang out?

30:18.441 --> 30:21.361
Anytime is fine for us,
so come over, okay?

30:21.444 --> 30:24.614
Right, we're going to invite
Jeong-in and her boyfriend over soon.

30:24.697 --> 30:26.366
You guys can all come over together.

30:26.449 --> 30:29.202
You prefer staying in anyway.

30:29.285 --> 30:32.580
And I have to head in for a shoot now.

30:33.665 --> 30:35.458
I'm running late. Let's hang out, okay?

30:35.542 --> 30:38.211
And honey, I'll see you at home.
See you later.

30:38.294 --> 30:39.170
Jae-in...

30:40.463 --> 30:41.714
will stay at our place.

30:44.425 --> 30:45.760
Sorry to inconvenience you.

30:46.010 --> 30:47.720
Jeong-in keeps pestering me.

30:49.430 --> 30:51.599
I see. That's not good.
Yes, stay at our place.

30:51.933 --> 30:54.561
- The shoot's about to start. I have to go.
- Okay, bye.

30:58.356 --> 30:59.691
You haven't changed at all.

31:02.235 --> 31:04.362
- Call me later.
- Okay.

31:06.447 --> 31:07.574
What's going on?

31:10.702 --> 31:11.953
We're getting a divorce.

31:18.543 --> 31:21.546
I asked you to come meet me today
to tell you that you should stay

31:21.629 --> 31:23.089
at my place for the time being.

31:25.633 --> 31:27.218
Okay, but why?

31:27.302 --> 31:29.596
What does it have to do
with you getting a divorce?

31:31.472 --> 31:32.807
We're not living together.

31:33.725 --> 31:36.436
But he comes by occasionally
when he's drunk and bothers me.

31:38.021 --> 31:39.856
So you want me to be your gatekeeper?

31:41.858 --> 31:43.318
I'll give you an allowance.

31:44.527 --> 31:45.695
That's a given.

31:47.822 --> 31:50.158
It won't be for long. Please do it for me.

31:52.076 --> 31:53.077
By the way,

31:53.494 --> 31:56.998
Si-hoon didn't seem to know about
Jeong-in wanting to break up with Gi-seok.

31:58.958 --> 32:01.169
I guess Gi-seok never showed it
in front of him.

32:02.337 --> 32:04.339
It'll take some time for them
to end things.

32:05.673 --> 32:08.384
Both of my sisters are in such a mess.

32:09.928 --> 32:11.262
What's wrong with Jeong-in?

32:14.140 --> 32:15.516
She's changed.

32:17.852 --> 32:19.812
I should meet up with her soon
and catch up.

32:19.896 --> 32:20.980
Not now.

32:24.317 --> 32:25.443
Give her some time.

32:27.570 --> 32:28.863
She's so confused right now.

32:31.658 --> 32:34.118
Then stay with her a little longer
and look after her.

32:36.496 --> 32:37.914
What if Si-hoon comes by again?

32:38.915 --> 32:40.458
Just look after Jeong-in for now.

32:51.636 --> 32:53.096
Gi-seok, did you have lunch?

32:54.055 --> 32:56.224
I couldn't find you
when I was going for lunch.

33:00.144 --> 33:01.145
What's wrong?

33:05.692 --> 33:07.151
Did something happen?

33:20.957 --> 33:21.958
No, it's nothing.

34:28.900 --> 34:32.570
DAD

35:45.059 --> 35:46.477
Are you not confident?

35:49.188 --> 35:50.648
You said you'll have regrets.

35:54.360 --> 35:56.195
I have to think about Eun-u as well.

35:57.530 --> 36:00.032
You still have a lot to learn
to become a real parent.

36:00.992 --> 36:02.618
One of the things that people hate

36:02.702 --> 36:04.787
among the comments
their parents often make is,

36:04.871 --> 36:07.165
"I gave up and sacrificed everything
for you."

36:07.248 --> 36:10.501
Do you think Eun-u will thank you
if you tell him when he's all grown up

36:10.585 --> 36:12.420
that you gave up dating because of him?

36:12.587 --> 36:14.005
That's not what I meant.

36:14.088 --> 36:16.924
Then why use Eun-u as an excuse?
That's so immature and petty.

36:17.675 --> 36:19.385
- Hye-jeong.
- Don't call me like that.

36:19.468 --> 36:21.554
Am I wrong? You're being so immature.

36:22.305 --> 36:25.933
My mom told me not to even dream
about dating someone who isn't like me.

36:26.142 --> 36:27.268
Don't be ridiculous.

36:27.518 --> 36:30.396
So? Are you saying you're torn
because of what your mother said?

36:33.441 --> 36:34.942
You said you want to be reckless.

36:35.026 --> 36:36.736
Go for it. I've got your back.

36:39.030 --> 36:40.615
Just do it, or you'll have regrets.

36:40.698 --> 36:43.117
If it doesn't work out,
you can give up then.

36:43.492 --> 36:44.785
She's too good for that.

36:47.121 --> 36:50.291
You're annoying the hell out of me.
I hope things don't work out, then.

36:52.001 --> 36:53.002
Bye.

37:12.271 --> 37:13.272
Hey, Gi-seok!

37:13.814 --> 37:15.483
- My gosh, hello.
- What?

37:15.566 --> 37:17.109
- Is that Gi-seok?
- Oh, my.

37:17.193 --> 37:18.778
- Long time no see.
- You're here too.

37:18.861 --> 37:21.030
- How have you been?
- What's gotten into you?

37:21.113 --> 37:23.407
Oh, I was in the area
and thought I should stop by.

37:24.575 --> 37:25.701
- I see.
- Nice to see you.

37:25.785 --> 37:28.287
How's your girlfriend?
You're still together, right?

37:28.371 --> 37:29.872
What was her name again?

37:29.956 --> 37:32.291
- Jeong-in?
- Oh, yes. Jeong-in.

37:32.375 --> 37:34.335
- You should've brought her.
- Yes.

37:34.710 --> 37:37.672
Well, next time. I'll get a beer too.

37:37.755 --> 37:38.839
Sure, just a second.

37:39.590 --> 37:40.967
Are you not getting married?

37:41.467 --> 37:43.678
We promised you
that we'd sing at your wedding.

37:43.761 --> 37:45.346
You'll have to tell us in advance.

37:45.763 --> 37:46.764
Okay, I will.

37:46.847 --> 37:49.684
Then let's see if you've still got it.

37:49.934 --> 37:51.978
- Yes, show us.
- Jeez, cut it out.

37:52.061 --> 37:53.479
Come on. Show us!

37:53.562 --> 37:56.065
- I quit playing guitar.
- That's bullshit.

37:56.148 --> 37:57.858
Then pick it up again. Come on!

38:01.112 --> 38:03.614
Hey, you've had this guitar for so long.

38:03.698 --> 38:05.032
It's a good guitar.

38:15.042 --> 38:16.127
Let's just drink.

38:16.210 --> 38:18.129
- Gosh, dude.
- You're such a downer.

38:19.672 --> 38:21.674
- I came here to drink.
- All right, cheers.

38:23.009 --> 38:24.176
It's good to see you.

38:29.640 --> 38:30.683
Why are you out here?

38:31.392 --> 38:32.476
Are you already drunk?

38:33.144 --> 38:34.520
No, I wanted some fresh air.

38:37.481 --> 38:38.566
What's going on?

38:41.193 --> 38:42.737
You obviously came

38:42.820 --> 38:44.363
because something's bothering you.

38:45.239 --> 38:46.282
No, nothing's going on.

38:48.284 --> 38:49.702
Do you regret quitting music?

38:51.037 --> 38:52.038
Cut it out, you prick.

38:53.414 --> 38:56.625
We're very proud of you
for doing so well for yourself.

38:59.462 --> 39:01.213
Let's get back inside and drink more.

39:05.551 --> 39:08.387
You said you told Mr. Kwon
that you don't want to get married.

39:09.472 --> 39:11.974
Then how come
he's not saying anything to us?

39:13.351 --> 39:15.311
Shall I make up whatever you want to hear?

39:15.728 --> 39:18.773
You're getting all snappy again.
Enough is enough, okay?

39:18.939 --> 39:21.901
I'm so sick and tired of having
to appease your dad all the time.

39:21.984 --> 39:23.903
Must I walk on eggshells even around you?

39:24.528 --> 39:25.571
I'm sorry.

39:26.989 --> 39:28.908
You say that when you have nothing to say.

39:29.825 --> 39:32.161
Hey, your dad is home. I have to go.

39:39.085 --> 39:40.711
I thought you had dinner plans.

39:40.878 --> 39:42.213
We called it an early night.

39:46.801 --> 39:47.843
Well...

39:48.511 --> 39:50.596
Jeong-in called earlier.

39:51.263 --> 39:53.641
- What did she say?
- She said the talk went well.

39:55.267 --> 39:56.352
Bullshit.

39:57.561 --> 40:00.648
Why? Did Mr. Kwon say something to you?

40:02.149 --> 40:04.527
- Did he?
- He wouldn't even look at me.

40:05.319 --> 40:07.405
What the heck did she say to him?

40:07.488 --> 40:09.782
Why is he treating me
like a useless mutt now?

40:11.325 --> 40:13.869
How could she be so self-centered?

40:14.620 --> 40:17.373
Well, she didn't say much,

40:17.623 --> 40:20.626
but she told him that she doesn't want
to get married right away.

40:21.419 --> 40:23.254
Then when is she going to get married?

40:23.337 --> 40:25.131
When she's 50?

40:27.007 --> 40:28.843
Tell her to just forget about it!

40:30.261 --> 40:33.431
I don't care anymore, so let her do
whatever the hell she wants to do!

40:58.164 --> 41:00.082
Are you just going to keep killing time?

41:01.375 --> 41:02.793
You need to sort things out.

41:03.794 --> 41:05.045
I know, I should.

41:07.298 --> 41:08.716
You know what's funny though?

41:09.842 --> 41:13.012
As for Ji-ho, I'm scared
that he might ignore my call.

41:14.138 --> 41:16.390
And as for Gi-seok,
I'm scared that he'll answer.

41:17.308 --> 41:19.560
You're not ready
to deal with him resenting you?

41:20.769 --> 41:22.104
That I can totally deal with.

41:23.939 --> 41:25.441
I don't know about other things,

41:26.108 --> 41:27.776
but one thing that bothers me is...

41:30.321 --> 41:32.239
After being together for years,

41:33.157 --> 41:34.783
it's ending in a way that's too...

41:36.285 --> 41:38.913
- Anyway, I don't feel good about it.
- It hasn't ended yet.

41:40.664 --> 41:44.251
It's never really over
until you see each other at your ugliest.

41:45.461 --> 41:47.755
- So we still have a long way to go?
- You sure do.

41:48.756 --> 41:51.592
First, you need to sort things out
with Ji-ho.

41:52.510 --> 41:54.470
I bet he was so turned off
by what you did.

41:56.305 --> 41:58.224
He probably doesn't want to see me again.

41:59.975 --> 42:02.353
Apologize to him in person
for hurting his feelings.

42:04.772 --> 42:06.607
What if I can't see him after that?

42:12.696 --> 42:13.739
Who is it?

42:15.407 --> 42:16.534
It's Ji-ho.

42:16.951 --> 42:18.786
Your last chance is happening so soon.

42:25.584 --> 42:26.627
Hello?

42:51.735 --> 42:53.612
How about the park we went to last time?

43:25.185 --> 43:26.770
Did I catch you at a bad time?

43:30.232 --> 43:31.567
What are you going to say?

43:35.029 --> 43:36.780
I'm not really here to talk.

43:38.991 --> 43:40.034
Then why are you here?

43:43.495 --> 43:44.580
I wanted to see you.

43:49.001 --> 43:50.002
What?

43:50.919 --> 43:53.839
Just be honest with me.
Don't tease me like this.

43:56.759 --> 43:58.135
I'm not following.

44:00.220 --> 44:01.472
I know you're mad at me.

44:04.850 --> 44:05.893
I was,

44:06.560 --> 44:09.647
but I was also worried you might use that
as an excuse and run away.

44:14.485 --> 44:15.944
Will you keep joking around?

44:16.904 --> 44:18.322
Do you think I'm stupid?

44:20.991 --> 44:22.785
I guess you really are a fool.

44:24.161 --> 44:26.205
I'm telling you the truth.
Why are you angry?

44:29.041 --> 44:30.292
That's really it?

44:31.669 --> 44:33.212
You wanted to see me? That's all?

44:37.132 --> 44:38.842
I should just date another woman.

44:43.305 --> 44:45.099
How could you believe that right away?

44:48.310 --> 44:49.395
You're so mean.

44:53.357 --> 44:55.192
We tend to pick up mean tricks quickly.

45:01.115 --> 45:03.826
I've decided to stop wondering
whether or not

45:05.369 --> 45:06.495
I deserve to ask you

45:08.080 --> 45:09.289
to be with me.

45:11.500 --> 45:15.212
No matter when you decide to come to me,
and even if you choose not to be with me,

45:16.422 --> 45:17.756
I'm just going to love you.

45:22.052 --> 45:23.137
I realized Yu Ji-ho

45:24.722 --> 45:25.764
loves...

45:28.350 --> 45:29.435
Lee Jeong-in.

45:40.070 --> 45:41.739
Will you cry again and say nothing?

48:36.788 --> 48:38.040
I checked everything.

48:38.373 --> 48:40.626
As for this, we were expecting it,

48:40.918 --> 48:42.419
- Mr. Kwon.
- so it should be okay.

48:43.337 --> 48:44.421
Someone's calling you.

48:45.297 --> 48:47.090
- Who is it?
- Nam Si-hoon.

48:47.507 --> 48:48.550
Just let it ring.

48:52.638 --> 48:54.389
If we enter this value, it becomes--

48:54.473 --> 48:56.433
But we e-mailed this to them,

48:57.100 --> 48:58.268
- didn't we?
- Yes, we did.

49:02.272 --> 49:03.607
- Hello.
- Hello.

49:08.946 --> 49:10.030
Oh, hello.

49:16.662 --> 49:18.956
I need to expand my clinic,
but I'm short of cash.

49:20.165 --> 49:22.334
Sell the house or something
and help me out.

49:26.213 --> 49:27.381
I'll pay you back, okay?

49:27.798 --> 49:30.550
Once I expand the clinic,
I'll get more patients in no time,

49:30.634 --> 49:32.844
- so I'll earn it back quickly.
- I have no money.

49:33.303 --> 49:35.138
And why do I have to get involved in it?

49:35.597 --> 49:36.765
We'll be divorced soon.

49:40.352 --> 49:42.646
Hey, you'd better listen to me. Okay?

49:43.271 --> 49:47.818
I won't divorce you even if your family
gets involved, so let's take the easy way.

49:47.901 --> 49:49.111
Lend me some money.

49:50.028 --> 49:53.365
As soon as the loan I asked Gi-seok
to look into gets approved,

49:53.448 --> 49:55.325
I'll pay you back right away.

49:56.493 --> 49:57.828
What's the problem?

49:58.537 --> 49:59.663
You've lost your mind.

50:03.542 --> 50:04.584
What's wrong?

50:08.171 --> 50:10.590
Don't do anything stupid. I'm warning you.

50:22.686 --> 50:23.729
Jae-in.

50:24.521 --> 50:25.647
What's up?

50:27.274 --> 50:28.817
I think Seo-in is pregnant.

50:29.943 --> 50:31.361
What? Did she say that to you?

50:31.695 --> 50:33.655
She asked me to pick up a pregnancy test.

50:34.156 --> 50:36.199
I got scared,
so I came to talk to you first.

50:39.661 --> 50:41.788
Can you leave now by any chance?

50:42.998 --> 50:44.082
Now?

50:52.174 --> 50:53.300
- Jeong-in.
- Yes.

50:53.925 --> 50:55.677
- Hey, I'm sorry.
- Don't be.

50:57.179 --> 50:59.097
- What about the manager?
- He has no idea.

50:59.681 --> 51:02.517
I feel as if I'm making you guys
aid in a crime or something.

51:02.601 --> 51:03.852
Come on. This is nothing.

51:04.603 --> 51:06.188
It's almost time to go home anyway.

51:07.147 --> 51:08.690
Oh, right. On my desk, there is--

51:08.774 --> 51:10.609
Yeong-ju is already taking care of it.

51:10.692 --> 51:13.361
As for the new releases,
I'll get as much done as possible.

51:14.237 --> 51:16.531
You've done a lot more for me.

51:17.199 --> 51:18.366
Don't make me feel bad.

51:18.533 --> 51:21.453
Keep feeling bad and just get going
before the manager sees you.

51:21.578 --> 51:23.538
I'll buy you lunch tomorrow. Thanks again.

51:23.622 --> 51:24.790
All right, get going.

51:39.137 --> 51:41.515
- Jeong-in, do you mind driving?
- No, not at all.

51:42.724 --> 51:44.434
- Sit in the back with Seo-in.
- Okay.

51:49.189 --> 51:50.732
I don't know for sure yet.

51:51.149 --> 51:52.609
I wanted to check just in case.

51:53.693 --> 51:56.571
What? I got so scared
that I ran to talk to Jeong-in right away.

51:56.655 --> 51:59.825
- She even left work early for you.
- Seo-in, how are you feeling now?

52:00.492 --> 52:01.618
I'm feeling much better.

52:02.160 --> 52:04.996
I was so dizzy earlier
that I couldn't drive.

52:05.914 --> 52:07.165
Could it be something else?

52:09.876 --> 52:12.212
I'll take a pregnancy test first
just to check.

52:12.295 --> 52:13.964
If it's not that, I'll see a doctor.

52:14.923 --> 52:17.217
Don't go alone.
Make sure you take Jae-in with you.

52:17.592 --> 52:18.552
All right.

52:18.844 --> 52:20.762
I shouldn't have come back from France.

52:23.265 --> 52:25.308
I'm being a nuisance today, aren't I?

52:26.309 --> 52:27.602
You're hurting my feelings.

52:27.686 --> 52:29.604
I'm just so grateful.

52:34.192 --> 52:37.529
I think Si-hoon is trying
to take out a loan through Gi-seok.

52:38.196 --> 52:40.532
Jeez, everything that guy does
irks me so much.

52:40.991 --> 52:42.826
Why didn't you tell him they broke up?

52:44.286 --> 52:45.412
They broke up?

52:47.122 --> 52:48.373
I'm trying to end things.

52:48.915 --> 52:50.500
- It'll take a while.
- Hey, Jae-in.

52:52.586 --> 52:55.797
Anyway, make sure
Gi-seok doesn't get involved.

52:55.964 --> 52:57.465
It'll only stress you out more.

52:58.925 --> 53:00.177
I know what you're saying.

53:03.013 --> 53:04.848
How about we have a nice meal together?

53:05.140 --> 53:06.600
Oh, I bought the thing.

53:06.683 --> 53:08.018
- Here.
- Give it to me later.

53:09.102 --> 53:11.771
Sure, let's do that.
Let's just have fun today.

53:12.272 --> 53:14.024
- Okay?
- Good?

53:14.107 --> 53:16.318
Can we have fun? For real?

53:16.568 --> 53:17.652
Yes, of course.

53:33.168 --> 53:34.252
Why aren't you eating?

53:35.629 --> 53:37.214
Hey, has Gi-seok figured it out?

53:38.465 --> 53:40.884
- What did he say?
- I'd rather have him say something.

53:41.509 --> 53:42.969
He wouldn't even talk to me.

53:45.430 --> 53:46.973
What? So he still doesn't know?

53:47.432 --> 53:50.101
That woman... I mean, Jeong-in
didn't say anything to you?

53:50.977 --> 53:51.937
No, she didn't.

53:52.771 --> 53:54.064
Then what could it be?

53:54.522 --> 53:55.941
Is it because of Nam Si-hoon?

53:56.816 --> 53:57.859
Who is that?

53:58.276 --> 53:59.486
He's a dentist.

54:00.987 --> 54:03.031
Oh, he must be Jeong-in's brother-in-law.

54:03.114 --> 54:04.449
What are you talking about?

54:05.325 --> 54:07.702
The news anchor, Lee Seo-in,
is her sister, you know.

54:12.290 --> 54:13.458
You guys didn't know?

54:14.042 --> 54:15.543
So... Hey.

54:16.294 --> 54:18.630
The news anchor, Lee Seo-in,
is Jae-in's sister?

54:18.713 --> 54:19.631
Yes.

54:21.633 --> 54:22.634
What's the matter?

54:24.010 --> 54:25.136
What about her?

54:25.971 --> 54:27.722
I heard she married a dentist.

54:28.640 --> 54:30.558
Nam Si-hoon must be that dentist.

54:31.059 --> 54:33.395
Well, he applied for a loan,

54:33.728 --> 54:35.146
but he doesn't qualify at all.

54:36.106 --> 54:38.358
It looks like
he keeps pestering Gi-seok about it.

54:39.234 --> 54:40.944
Gi-seok even ignored his call today.

54:42.195 --> 54:45.448
The thing is though, if his application
for the loan can't be approved,

54:45.532 --> 54:47.158
Gi-seok can just explain it to him.

54:47.242 --> 54:50.078
Why would he ignore his call?

54:51.496 --> 54:52.831
Are they on bad terms now?

54:55.875 --> 54:56.960
Hey, what's wrong?

54:57.502 --> 55:00.088
Don't mind me.
Hey, maybe Gi-seok has figured it out.

55:00.338 --> 55:01.423
Why do you say that?

55:02.048 --> 55:03.550
He's avoiding her brother-in-law,

55:03.633 --> 55:05.385
so they're probably not on good terms.

55:06.678 --> 55:08.054
My gosh, Yeong-jae.

55:08.888 --> 55:11.725
You're so smart. I don't get
why you fail the exam every year.

55:12.726 --> 55:14.060
I don't get it either. Jeez.

55:17.522 --> 55:21.943
WOORI PHARMACY

56:11.451 --> 56:12.952
Where is Ji-ho's place?

56:13.495 --> 56:14.621
Send me his address.

57:44.752 --> 57:45.712
Yes.

57:46.087 --> 57:47.797
Gi-seok is there? What did he say?

57:47.922 --> 57:50.300
He didn't come in.
He's in front of the building now.

57:50.383 --> 57:51.718
Did you tell him you're here?

57:54.554 --> 57:56.222
He's probably there to see Ji-ho.

57:56.598 --> 57:58.141
Does he know that he lives here?

58:00.143 --> 58:02.520
- I don't know.
- What do I do? Go out and talk to him?

58:02.604 --> 58:04.355
What do I say to him though?

58:06.191 --> 58:07.901
Yeong-ju, I'll call you right back.

58:21.873 --> 58:23.041
Hi, Jeong-in.

58:23.833 --> 58:26.377
- Where are you?
- I'm on my way home.

58:31.257 --> 58:32.342
Is it about Gi-seok?

58:33.801 --> 58:34.928
You already know?

58:35.970 --> 58:36.971
Yes.

58:39.098 --> 58:41.309
- I'll head over there now, so--
- Don't come.

58:43.228 --> 58:44.229
Ji-ho.

58:46.397 --> 58:48.566
We knew
I'd have to talk to him at least once.

58:49.692 --> 58:51.277
Don't worry. I'll handle him.

58:52.737 --> 58:54.781
No, that's not right. I'll go sort it out.

58:56.616 --> 58:57.784
This is my problem.

58:59.244 --> 59:00.745
I have a favor to ask you though.

59:02.247 --> 59:03.289
What is it?

59:03.790 --> 59:07.418
I want to be honest and tell everything.

59:08.586 --> 59:09.712
Can I do that?

59:11.798 --> 59:12.840
Yes.

59:13.424 --> 59:15.843
Then it's all good. Don't worry.

59:17.220 --> 59:18.763
How can I not worry?

59:20.807 --> 59:22.100
Then keep worrying about it.

59:23.268 --> 59:24.769
How could you crack a joke now?

59:25.603 --> 59:27.564
I'm just trying to tell you it'll be fine.

59:28.106 --> 59:30.108
Don't worry too much. I'll call you later.

59:32.485 --> 59:33.528
I'm sorry.

59:34.529 --> 59:35.613
For liking me?

59:37.156 --> 59:38.241
Gosh, stop it.

59:41.536 --> 59:42.787
Put your worries to rest.

59:46.165 --> 59:47.417
You have to call me, okay?

59:48.293 --> 59:49.294
All right.

59:50.920 --> 59:52.130
Talk to you later, then.

01:00:03.808 --> 01:00:05.018
You should eat more.

01:00:05.685 --> 01:00:07.770
This is the biggest meal I've had
as of late.

01:00:10.523 --> 01:00:11.566
What's wrong?

01:00:13.234 --> 01:00:15.069
Gi-seok went to see Ji-ho.

01:00:16.237 --> 01:00:17.238
My gosh.

01:00:18.615 --> 01:00:19.657
Ji-ho?

01:00:21.451 --> 01:00:22.994
It's the guy she's crazy about.

01:00:23.870 --> 01:00:25.246
Why does he want to meet him?

01:00:25.913 --> 01:00:27.165
Because of you?

01:00:27.915 --> 01:00:29.584
It's obviously because of Jeong-in.

01:00:30.960 --> 01:00:32.879
What if Gi-seok beats him up to a pulp?

01:00:35.256 --> 01:00:37.717
They're adults,
so they won't behave like kids.

01:00:37.800 --> 01:00:40.720
You never know. People can do anything
when they're pissed off.

01:00:42.847 --> 01:00:44.057
Don't you have to go?

01:00:45.350 --> 01:00:46.726
Ji-ho told me not to come.

01:00:46.809 --> 01:00:48.102
Of course.

01:00:48.353 --> 01:00:50.396
They won't be able to talk
if you're there.

01:00:51.105 --> 01:00:52.649
I should've been more thoughtful.

01:00:53.483 --> 01:00:55.360
I shouldn't have given it away like that.

01:00:56.736 --> 01:00:58.196
Gi-seok was bound to find out.

01:00:59.155 --> 01:01:00.948
I know, but now is not the right time.

01:02:38.796 --> 01:02:40.047
They're gone.

01:02:40.131 --> 01:02:42.759
Hey, what if they're fighting
in an empty lot or something?

01:02:42.842 --> 01:02:44.260
This isn't about winning.

01:02:44.343 --> 01:02:46.471
You're wreaking havoc on a woman's life,

01:02:46.554 --> 01:02:48.848
and I'm simply trying to stop that.

01:02:49.599 --> 01:02:52.143
You'd better stop acting up
when I'm warning you nicely.

01:02:52.310 --> 01:02:54.437
Jeong-in and I will marry
before the year ends.

01:02:54.520 --> 01:02:55.980
Oh, you'll tell him about us?

01:02:56.063 --> 01:02:58.441
What about Ji-ho?
You'll tell him all about that too?

01:02:58.524 --> 01:03:00.443
I can't let you choose the wrong path.

01:03:00.526 --> 01:03:01.611
Damn it!

01:03:01.736 --> 01:03:04.822
So what kind of man are you talking about?

01:03:04.906 --> 01:03:07.575
Someone who has a warm heart.
There's someone I like.

01:03:07.658 --> 01:03:10.578
You said she's never been married.
I told you to give up on her.

01:03:11.245 --> 01:03:12.330
What are you thinking?

01:03:12.830 --> 01:03:15.416
What do you think will happen to us?

01:03:15.708 --> 01:03:16.876
I'm in trouble.

01:03:17.001 --> 01:03:19.462
I love you, Ji-ho.
